The committee met with the party's top 6 and provincial chairs and secretaries on Tuesday after Jacob Zuma's Cabinet reshuffle. JOHANNESBURG - After a tumultuous few days that saw President Jacob Zuma reshuffle his Cabinet and South Africa's subsequent downgrade to junk status, the African National Congress (ANC) has briefed the media on its national working committee (NWC) meeting. The committee met with the party's top six and ANC provincial chairpersons and secretaries on Tuesday for the first time since Zuma reshuffled his Cabinet, angering some of his colleagues in the top six.WATCH: ANC national working committee briefing